<item>
            <title>[LU-17965] PCC: reopen the PCC copy for fallback file handle</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17965</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a file is attaching and copying data from Lustre OSTs to PCC copy, the file is in PCC attaching state. New open and I/O on the same file will fallback to Lustre OSTs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once the file finished the PCC attach and valid cached on PCC backend, the new I/O for the fallback file handle is still issuing to Lustre OSTs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case, we could reopen the PCC copy, and direct the I/O to PCC copy instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
